  "text": "Egbe et al [CITATION_1] identified BPVT in 46 out of 397 (11%) bioprosthetic valves explanted at Mayo Clinic, which also suggested BPVT to be more frequent cause of bioprosthesis dysfunction. In contrast to the misconception that BPVT is a perioperative phenomenon, Egbe's study also revealed that 65% of all reoperations were due to BPVT, occurred more than 1 year after implantation, and up to 15% of these reoperations occurred more than 5 years after implantation.",
